        <h1>Early evening Metropolitan and Piccadilly line closures west of Rayners Lane</h1>
        <div class="content-page-press-release">
        26 June 2006
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        Metropolitan and Piccadilly line services will be suspended west of Rayners Lane from 21:00 on Tuesday 4 and Wednesday 5 July.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<div class="pullquote right">
                        <p>
                            Early evening closure of these lines is necessary to enable Metronet to carry out work
                            
                        </p>
                    </div>
                
            
            
            <p>There will be no service on:</p>
<ul>
<li>The Metropolitan line between Uxbridge and Ruislip 
</li><li>The Piccadilly line between Uxbridge and Rayners Lane</li></ul>
<p>Early evening closure of these lines is necessary to enable Metronet to carry out work to eliminate heat related temporary speed restrictions in place between Uxbridge and Ickenham. </p>
<p>London Underground agreed to the early closures after Metronet failed to complete the work in regular engineering hours ahead of summer.</p>
<p>A replacement bus service will operate from Uxbridge to Ruislip at 10 minute intervals. </p>
<p>Customer Information Assistants will be available to assist passengers at all stations served by the replacement bus. </p>
<p>Valid London Underground tickets will be accepted on local bus routes between Uxbridge and Rayners Lane.</p>
<p>Piccadilly line trains will operate every 20 minutes between Acton Town and Rayners Lane during the closure.</p>
<p>Passengers are advised to add an additional 30 minutes to their journey time.</p>
<p>For 24-hour information on all London travel, please call: 020-7222 1234 or visit Transport for London's website: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk">www.tfl.gov.uk</a> </p>
<p>
